{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04244/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04244"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:44"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man ties the strings of a coat on a fashion model."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04244","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04244"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1/2da056de-0059-400b-afd0-ccfd902e22d5","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:27:11.224Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Daniel Day-Lewis spent a year preparing for the role of Reynolds Woodcock, training in dressmaking under New York City Ballet costume designer Marc Happel and ultimately reproducingby hand a dress by Cristóbal Balenciaga. See Jack Moss’s “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW43862749 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.anothermag.com/fashion-beauty/10539/the-real-life-couturiers-who-inspired-phantom-thread\"><u>The Real-Life Couturiers Who Inspired </u><em><u>Phantom Thread</u></em></a>” for a summary of three potential inspiration from the world of English haute couture on the film, as well as Focus Features’ press materials, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW43862749 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.focusfeatures.com/article/background_phantom-thread_-fashion-designers\"><u>The Haute Couture World of </u><em><u>Phantom Thread</u></em></a>,” for another list of four.&nbsp;</p><p>A part of the fashion show, the dress numbers underscore how the women in these situations and in the world of haute couture fashion houses were material and commodities. In this way, theyfunction similarly to the measurements in the scene when Alma meets Cyril. This detail also seems to be drawn from Mary Blume’s biography of Cristóbal Balenciaga: “Like Vionnet, Balenciaga wanted his models to be remote rather than appealing, gazing over the heads of clients and casually carrying a card on which the number of the outfit—unlike other designers, he never gave his clothes names—was displayed” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>,34).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04244/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:290.71332436069997,190.49798115746978,759.7308209959622,692.5437415881561"}}}]}]}]}